excerpt: Well-known alpine destination with a ski resort, glaciers & cable car rides offering scenic views.
detail_description: Zugspitze is a well-known alpine destination that offers a ski resort, glaciers, and cable car rides with breathtaking scenic views. The area features a historic building constructed by Adolf Wenz in the late 19th century, which includes a weather station and former royal high observatory. Visitors can experience the thrill of ascending Germany's highest mountain via cog railway and cable car.
name: Zugspitze

excerpt: Dramatic, clear-water mountain lake with a popular hiking loop, boating & a restaurant.
detail_description: Eibsee is a breathtaking mountain lake located in the Wetterstein Mountains, known for its crystal-clear, deep blue waters. It is a popular destination for outdoor enthusiasts, offering a picturesque hiking loop and opportunities for boating. The area surrounding Eibsee is rich in natural beauty and serves as the gateway to the Alps, with easy access to Zugspitze, Germany's highest peak. Visitors can also enjoy modern amenities such as restaurants and hotels while experiencing Bavarian traditions and craftsmanship.
name: Eibsee

excerpt: Scenic gorge along the Partnach River featuring waterfalls & river rapids, plus walking paths.
detail_description: Partnach Gorge, located along the Partnach River, is a stunning natural wonder with waterfalls and river rapids. To reach this beautiful place, you can take a train from Munich central station to Garmisch Partenkirchen and then a bus to the stadium before walking for about 10 minutes to the entrance. The trail through the gorge is relatively easy and offers breathtaking views of the surrounding environment.
name: Partnach Gorge

excerpt: Extending from a cliffside, this popular lookout platform offers panoramic mountain & valley views.
detail_description: AlpspiX is a popular lookout platform that offers breathtaking panoramic views of the mountains and valleys. It was opened in July 2010 and features two steel footbridges crossing over each other in the shape of an X, protruding 25 meters off the side of the mountain. The platform provides superb views of Zugspitze and the surrounding mountains, as well as a panorama of Hollental valley 1000 meters below.
name: Alpspix

excerpt: This narrow, scenic gorge with waterfalls & a walkway is a popular hiking destination.
detail_description: Partnachklamm, located in Garmisch-Partenkirchen, is a narrow and picturesque gorge featuring waterfalls and a walkway, making it a popular destination for hikers. During winter, torch hiking tours are available in the area, offering an exciting way to experience the beauty of the gorge. The 703m long and 80m high Alpine wonder provides breathtaking views of spraying waterfalls, rapids, and calm basins.
name: Partnachklamm

excerpt: Garmisch-Partenkirchen is a German ski resort in Bavaria, formed when 2 towns united in 1935. It's a prominent destination for skiing and ice skating as well as hiking. The town lies near the Zugspitze, Germany's highest peak, with a 2,962m summit accessed by cogwheel train and cable car. Garmisch is considered the more fashionable section, while Partenkirchen's cobblestone streets retain a traditional Bavarian feel.
detail_description: Garmisch-Partenkirchen, a renowned German ski resort in Bavaria, is the result of the merger of two towns. It's a popular destination for skiing, ice skating, and hiking, located near Zugspitze, Germany's highest peak. Garmisch is known for its modern vibe while Partenkirchen maintains a traditional Bavarian feel with its cobblestone streets.
name: Garmisch-Partenkirchen

excerpt: Cobblestone avenue lined with shops & eateries in ornate, pastel buildings adorned with murals.
detail_description: Ludwigstraße is the historical main street of Partenkirchen, known for its traditional Bavarian architecture and old-world charm. The cobblestone avenue is lined with ornate pastel buildings adorned with colorful murals, housing numerous local shops, restaurants, inns, and more.
name: Ludwigstraße

excerpt: Modern structure on site of a 1920s ski jump, with a 100m-long start tower, hosting weekly tours.
detail_description: The Olympic Ski Jump, located in Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Germany, is a modern structure built on the site of a 1920s ski jump. It features a 100m-long start tower and hosts weekly tours for visitors. The stadium gained international fame during the 1936 Olympic Games and continues to be a popular attraction today. Situated in the Bavarian Alps, it offers a glimpse into Germany's sporting history and hosts various international and local sporting events.
name: Olympic Ski Jump

excerpt: 2,628-m. pyramidal limestone mountain popular with hikers, climbers, mountain bikers & paragliders.
detail_description: Alpspitze is a 2,628-meter pyramidal limestone mountain that attracts hikers, climbers, mountain bikers, and paragliders. It is located near Garmisch-Partenkirchen and can be reached by a funicular and cable car. The area also offers ski slopes at the top lift of 2050 meters and the Kreuzeck which is linked by a lift.
name: Alpspitze

excerpt: Museum in a 17th-century merchant's house exploring local history & culture, with folk art & a shop.
detail_description: Museum Werdenfels is a captivating attraction located in the charming town of Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Germany. Housed in a 17th-century merchant's home, this museum offers an immersive experience into the local history and culture of the Werdenfels region. Visitors can explore a diverse collection of artifacts including archaeological finds from ancient trade routes, religious objects, carnival masks, folk art, and antique furnishings.
name: Museum Werdenfels

detail_description: The Michael Ende Kurpark, located in the heart of Garmisch-Partenkirchen, is a serene and picturesque space dedicated to the life and literary works of the renowned German author, Michael Ende. Visitors can enjoy a tranquil environment surrounded by lush greenery, flower beds, and charming lily ponds inhabited by goldfish. The park offers an immersive experience with nature, featuring pathways adorned with pretty flowers and opportunities for barefoot walks on soft moss and smooth pebbles.
name: Michael-Ende-Kurpark

excerpt: Verdant peak, popular with paragliders, with sweeping mountain views, trails & cable car access.
detail_description: Wank is a popular destination for outdoor enthusiasts, offering activities such as paragliding, skiing, and hiking. The area features sweeping mountain views and access to trails and cable cars. Skiing options are available at Eckbauer and Wank, with beginner-friendly slopes and lifts reaching heights of 21780 meters (5850 feet) at Wank.
name: Wank

excerpt: Mittenwald is a town amid the Alpine peaks of Bavaria, Germany. It's known for its colorful painted houses and its violin-making history, documented in the central Geigenbaumuseum. The 18th-century St. Peter and St. Paul Church is famed for its colorful frescoes. To the west, forested paths pass Lautersee Lake and the Laintal waterfall. In the northwest, Hoher Kranzberg’s slopes have trails and lookouts.
detail_description: Mittenwald, a charming town nestled in the Bavarian Alps of Germany, is famous for its vibrant painted houses and rich history of violin-making, showcased at the Geigenbaumuseum. The 18th-century St. Peter and St. Paul Church features stunning frescoes. Surrounding the town are scenic paths leading to Lautersee Lake and the Laintal waterfall to the west, while Hoher Kranzberg offers trails and viewpoints to the northwest.
name: Mittenwald

detail_description: Garmisch-Classic is a stunning ski resort consisting of three impressive mountains: Hausberg, Kreuzeck, and Alpspitze. It caters to skiers of all levels, offering mostly easy-to-moderate runs on the Hausberg for families and beginners. The resort provides diverse ski runs and slopes suitable for everyone, including kids and professional skiers. In addition to skiing, visitors can enjoy activities like tobogganing and cross-country skiing during the winter season.
name: Garmisch-Classic

detail_description: Nestled in the picturesque town of Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Wallfahrtskirche St. Anton is a stunning example of Rococo architecture, constructed between 1708 and 1738. This beautiful pilgrimage church features an eye-catching onion dome that can be seen from afar. Originally home to a small chapel built by cousins Jakob and Johann Lidl in the 17th century, it was transformed into its current form after the Spanish War of Succession.
name: Wallfahrtskirche St. Anton

detail_description: The Richard-Strauss-Institut, located in Garmisch, is a tribute to the life and work of the renowned composer Richard Strauss. Although his former home is not open to visitors, this institute offers a popular exhibition dedicated to Strauss's life. The institute becomes the focal point during the annual Richard-Strauss-Tage music festival held in mid-June, featuring concerts and lectures on the composer.
name: Richard-Strauss-Institut

excerpt: Rising 1,651m above sea level, this mountain features a ski resort with an Olympic course.
detail_description: Kreuzeck is a stunning mountain in Bavaria, rising 1,651m above sea level and featuring a ski resort with an Olympic course. It is reached by a funicular and cable car from Garmisch-Partenkirchen. The area offers popular ski slopes like Alpspitz and Kreuzeck, which are lift-linked.
name: Kreuzeck

detail_description: Garmisch-Partenkirchen City Centre is a charming destination located just a short walk from the train station and cable car to Zugspitze Mountain. The area offers a mix of traditional Bavarian decor and classic 19th-century style in its accommodations, some with stunning mountain views. Visitors can enjoy delicious Bavarian cuisine and seafood specialties at the local restaurants.
name: Garmisch-Partenkirchen City Centre

excerpt: This small mountaintop castle with dramatic views was completed in 1872 for King Ludwig II.
detail_description: Nestled at an impressive elevation of 1,866 meters in the breathtaking Wetterstein massif, Könighaus am Schachen is a charming mountaintop retreat that offers visitors a glimpse into the opulent world of King Ludwig II. Completed in 1872, this enchanting wooden palace showcases authentic Swiss chalet architecture and features five cozy rooms on its lower level along with a stunning Moorish hall above.
name: Könighaus am Schachen

excerpt: Picturesque natural area offering 3 steep, rocky waterfalls & forested walking trails.
detail_description: Kuhflucht Waterfalls, located near Farchant in Germany, is a stunning natural attraction featuring three steep and rocky waterfalls set amidst forested walking trails. These falls are among the tallest in the country, with a height of 270 meters. The area offers picturesque views of Garmisch and the Zugspitze, making it perfect for outdoor enthusiasts and photography lovers.
name: Kuhfluchtwasserfälle

excerpt: Grainau is a municipality in the district of Garmisch-Partenkirchen, in southern Bavaria, Germany. It is located at the foot of the Zugspitze mountain, the tallest mountain in Germany in the sub-mountain range of the Wetterstein Alps which is a branch off the main mountain range it is connected to, the Alps. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Grainau, situated in the southern Bavaria district of Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Germany, is a charming municipality nestled at the base of Zugspitze, Germany's highest peak within the Wetterstein Alps. The area offers breathtaking views and is an ideal destination for nature enthusiasts.
name: Grainau

excerpt: Hiking paths wind through this unique, deep gorge with waterfalls, ice chunks, bridges & tunnels.
detail_description: Höllentalklamm, also known as the Hell Valley gorge or Hollental Valley, is a unique natural wonder located just six kilometers southwest of Garmisch-Partenkirchen. The gorge features hiking paths that lead through deep ravines with waterfalls, ice chunks, bridges, and tunnels. Visitors can follow trails to the summit at 1,045 meters and explore numerous tunnels and bridges along the way.
name: Höllentalklamm

excerpt: Small lake framed by mountains with a perimeter hiking trail, swimming, ice skating & boat rentals.
detail_description: Nestled amidst the stunning Alpine mountains, Riessersee is a picturesque lake offering a variety of activities such as hiking along its perimeter trail, swimming in its clear waters, and even ice skating during winter. This small body of water has a rich history dating back to medieval times when it was artificially created in a forest glade. It gained international recognition as the venue for skating and ice hockey events during the 1936 Winter Olympics.
name: Riessersee

detail_description: Eckbauerbahn is a popular cable car and mountain destination, perfect for families with children. The area offers stunning panoramic views of the Alps and provides sled rentals for an enjoyable experience with young ones. Additionally, visitors can find a restaurant and playground at the top, making it an ideal spot for families to spend quality time together. Despite initial concerns about pricing, many agree that the breathtaking views and overall experience make it well worth the cost.
name: Eckbauerbahn

excerpt: Woodsy eatery with a spacious terrace serving heaping traditional dishes & housemade desserts.
detail_description: Kaiserschmarrn-Alm is a charming eatery nestled in the woods, offering a spacious terrace for dining. The restaurant provides indoor and outdoor seating, making it an ideal spot to enjoy traditional dishes and housemade desserts while taking in breathtaking views. A popular choice among visitors is the Kaiserschmarrn, a pancake-like dish topped with powdered sugar and caramelized almonds, served with applesauce on the side.
name: Kaiserschmarrn-Alm

detail_description: Hausberg is a budget-friendly skiing destination with convenient equipment rental options at the bottom of the Hausberg gondola. It caters to both beginners and experts, offering a variety of ski runs in different difficulty levels. The mountain provides ample opportunities for learning, with flat transition areas for beginners. Additionally, visitors can access other mountains from Hausberg. For non-skiers, taking a ticket up to Zugspitze offers stunning views and the chance to enjoy mulled wine.
name: Hausberg

detail_description: The Hammersbacher Fußweg is a picturesque hiking trail that winds through the beautiful German countryside. This scenic path offers stunning views of lush greenery, charming villages, and rolling hills. The trail is well-maintained and suitable for hikers of all skill levels, making it a perfect destination for nature enthusiasts and outdoor adventurers. Along the way, hikers can immerse themselves in the tranquility of the natural surroundings while enjoying the fresh air and peaceful ambiance.
name: Hammersbacher Fußweg

detail_description: Wamberg is a charming mountain village in Germany, offering picturesque views and an ideal starting point for hiking. Accessible only by car via a steep, narrow road, it provides a tranquil setting away from the crowds. The village boasts an idyllic atmosphere with its church open on Sundays and a welcoming inn serving delicious meals. Visitors can enjoy beautiful hikes amidst stunning landscapes of fields, forests, and mountains while being surrounded by farms.
name: Wamberg

detail_description: Höllental is a must-visit destination for experienced hikers, offering a challenging circuit that takes you through stunning waterfalls, rock formations, and ancient forests. The trail culminates in a spectacular view of the Zugspitze, making it an unforgettable experience for nature enthusiasts.
name: Höllental

excerpt: Established in 1930, this snug house museum & workshop features exhibits on the history of violins.
detail_description: The Geigenbaumuseum, also known as the Violin Making Museum, was established in 1930 and is located in Mittenwald, Germany. The museum showcases the history of violin making and its connection to the village. Visitors can explore exhibits featuring violins from different time periods and learn about the craft of handcrafting violins. The museum is housed in a historic building dating back to the 1700s, adding to its charm.
name: Geigenbaumuseum

detail_description: Pfarrkirche St. Martin, also known as the Old Church, has a rich history dating back to the 9th century. The current Gothic building, constructed in 1280, features remarkable wall paintings including a larger-than-life figure of St. Christopher and a Passion of the Christ fresco from the 14th century. The Parish Church of St.
name: Pfarrkirche St. Martin

detail_description: The Garmisch Olympia Ice Skating Rink is a great place to go ice skating if you're looking for a fun and adrenaline-filled experience. The rink is well maintained and has plenty of space for all types of skaters, from beginners to experts. Plus, the staff are friendly and trained in various skill ranges, so your family can have lots of fun no matter their level of expertise.
name: Garmisch Olympia Ice Sport Stadium

excerpt: Vast, scenic mountain range hugging the German-Austrian border & known for hiking & skiing.
detail_description: The Bavarian Alps, a vast and picturesque mountain range along the German-Austrian border, are renowned for their opportunities for hiking and skiing. The region offers stunning views of dramatic peaks, lush valleys, and charming villages. Garmisch-Partenkirchen is a popular destination within the Bavarian Alps, serving as both a ski resort in winter and a hub for summer activities like hiking and climbing.
name: Bavarian Alps

detail_description: Lermoos is a charming village located in the Austrian Alps, offering stunning mountain views and a peaceful atmosphere. Visitors can enjoy outdoor activities such as hiking, mountain biking, and paragliding in the surrounding area. The village has traditional architecture, cozy accommodations, and local restaurants serving delicious Tyrolean cuisine. Lermoos is also known for its beautiful alpine lake, perfect for swimming and relaxation during the summer months.
name: Lermoos

excerpt: Ehrwald is a municipality in the district of Reutte in the Austrian state of Tyrol. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Ehrwald, located in the Tyrol state of Austria, is a charming municipality in the district of Reutte. It is part of a scenic route that connects some of Tyrol's top attractions, such as Mayrhofen, Zillertal Alps, Lake Achensee, Karwendel mountains, and the Mieming Range.
name: Ehrwald

excerpt: Ettal is a German municipality and a village in the district of Garmisch-Partenkirchen in Bavaria. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Ettal, located in the picturesque district of Garmisch-Partenkirchen in Bavaria, is a charming German municipality and village. With its rich history and stunning natural surroundings, Ettal offers visitors a delightful blend of cultural experiences and outdoor adventures.
name: Ettal

excerpt: Summit plateau reached by cable car, with far-reaching views, hiking trails & paragliding.
detail_description: Wankbahn is a popular landmark in Garmisch-Partenkirchen, offering a summit plateau reached by cable car with stunning panoramic views, hiking trails, and paragliding opportunities. Visitors can immerse themselves in the city's rich history and culture by exploring nearby attractions such as Partnachklamm, Graseckseilbahn, Burgruine Werdenfels, and Spielbank Garmisch-Partenkirchen.
name: Wankbahn

detail_description: Kurpark Garmisch is a delightful oasis nestled in the heart of Garmisch-Partenkirchen, offering visitors a serene escape from the bustling shopping district. This charming park features stunning floral displays, including vibrant primroses and pansies that bloom beautifully throughout the seasons. A picturesque walking path meanders along the icy blue Loisach River, showcasing its glacial origins and providing a tranquil backdrop for leisurely strolls.
name: Kurpark Garmisch

excerpt: Biberwier is a municipality with 612 inhabitants in the district of Reutte in the Austrian state of Tyrol. The municipality is located in the district court Reutte. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Biberwier, a charming municipality nestled in the district of Reutte in the Austrian state of Tyrol, is home to around 612 residents. This picturesque destination is situated within the district court Reutte, offering visitors a tranquil and idyllic setting to explore.
name: Biberwier

excerpt: Easily accessed from many German cities, this mountain range is popular for outdoor pursuits.
detail_description: Wetterstein, a mountain range in Germany, is easily accessible from various cities and is a popular destination for outdoor activities. The area features the picturesque Kleiner See at an elevation of 785 meters, with a hotel offering a terrace overlooking the lake. Visitors can enjoy stunning views while walking around the lake on a 20-minute trail.
name: Wetterstein

detail_description: The restaurant Tannenhütte overlooks Zugspitze, Bavaria's highest peak. The modern-designed hut features stunning views and delicious food from soups to schnitzel, roast beef, and their own cakes. After a short hike you can reach a thrilling suspension bridge for hikers.
name: Tannenhütte

excerpt: Casual restaurant with an industrial-chic vibe specializing in burgers, fries & cocktails.
detail_description: Shaka Burgerhouse is a trendy, casual restaurant located in Garmisch-Partenkirchen, offering a variety of burgers, fries, and cocktails in an industrial-chic setting. The menu features American classics such as juicy burgers, crispy fries, hearty sandwiches, steaks, and organic dishes. The restaurant also caters to vegans with a selection of vegan and vegetarian options including the MEGAN'S VEGAN BURGER.
name: Shaka Burgerhouse

excerpt: A big menu of pizza, pasta & Italian mains at a rustic, wood-paneled trattoria with a terrace.
detail_description: La Baita is an Italian restaurant located in the center of Garmisch-Partenkirchen, offering a diverse menu featuring pizza, pasta, and other Italian dishes. The rustic trattoria with a wood-paneled interior also has a terrace for outdoor dining. While the restaurant offers some vegan options, they mainly consist of dishes without cheese. Visitors can enjoy delicious Italian cuisine in a great environment, with a non-smoking area available outside for families and non-smokers to enjoy.
name: La Baita

excerpt: Classic eatery offering familiar fare like sauerbraten & schnitzel, plus Bavarian dishes.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Garmisch, Hofbräustüberl Garmisch is a charming eatery that captures the essence of Bavarian culture. This rustic pub invites you to indulge in classic dishes like sauerbraten and schnitzel, alongside other beloved regional specialties. The atmosphere is warm and inviting, perfect for enjoying a leisurely meal while soaking up live Bavarian music that enhances your dining experience.
name: Hofbräustüberl Garmisch

excerpt: Wood-oven pizza, pasta & grill dishes at a simple, modern space with a terrace on the town square.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Restaurant Pizzeria Renzo is a delightful Italian eatery that promises an authentic culinary experience. With its inviting wood-oven pizzas, fresh pasta, and grilled dishes served in a modern yet simple setting, it’s the perfect spot to unwind after exploring the town square. The terrace offers a lovely view while you savor their extensive menu featuring everything from seafood to hearty steaks and delectable salads.
name: Restaurant Pizzeria Renzo

excerpt: Traditional dishes, housemade cakes & wine served in a relaxed restaurant with a terrace.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Maronis is a delightful restaurant that captures the essence of traditional dining with a modern twist. This charming eatery boasts an impressive menu featuring everything from classic schnitzels to exquisite Asian dishes, ensuring there's something for every palate. Guests can unwind on the inviting terrace while sipping on refreshing cocktails or indulging in housemade cakes and fine wines from their small but well-curated vinothek.
name: Maronis

excerpt: Huge portions of Bavarian standards like schnitzel & cheese spaetzle in a traditional tavern.
detail_description: Wolpertinger is a traditional tavern located in Garmisch, offering huge portions of Bavarian standards such as schnitzel and cheese spaetzle. The restaurant also serves original local specialties and features vintage south-Bavarian interior design. Visitors have praised the friendly and welcoming staff, as well as the incredible vibes, food, and service.
name: Wolpertinger

detail_description: The cafe Wildkaffee Café is a great place to get coffee and snacks. They serve their own roasted beans and blends, and have an array of sandwiches to choose from. The staff is incredibly helpful, and they speak English very well. It's also within a short walk of the main train station.
name: Wildkaffee Café

detail_description: Pfleger-See is a picturesque lake located near the impressive Konigsstand mountain range, making it a popular destination for locals and visitors alike. The hike to the lake is relatively easy and suitable for families with small children or baby carriages. At Berggasthof Pflegersee hut, visitors can take a break and enjoy stunning views of the lake. In winter, when some lakes freeze solid, Pfleger-See offers the opportunity for ice skating amidst breathtaking mountain views.
name: Pfleger-See

detail_description: Badersee, a stunning emerald green mountain lake located at the foot of Zugspitze Mountain in Grainau, Bavaria, is a favorite travel destination for many tourists. The lake is about 18 meters deep and has a wild and raw feel to it. Shoals of trout can be seen under its clear water, amidst fallen branches and tree trunks. One bank of the lake features a hotel while the rest remains untouched.
name: Badersee
